==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Felon
<hw>Fel"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE., adj., cruel,
<pos>n.</pos>, villain, ruffian, traitor, whitlow, F.
<ets>f⟦eacute⟧lon</ets> traitor, in OF. also, villain, fr. LL.
<ets>felo</ets>. See Fell, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A person who has committed a felony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person guilty or capable of heinous
crime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A kind of whitlow; a painful
imflammation of the periosteum of a finger, usually of the last
joint.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Criminal; convict; malefactor; culprit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Felon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Felon
<hw>Fel"on</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Characteristic of a felon;
malignant; fierce; malicious; cruel; traitorous; disloyal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vain shows of love to vail his felon hate.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Felonious</ent>⟦br⟧
